Description: Shoulder sherd of East Greek pottery oinochoe; exterior: glazed black (fired streaky brown); inscription on exterior.
Curator's comments: The number in Petrie's catalogue, 228, is written on the exterior surface of the sherd.
Bibliographic references: Petrie 1886 / Naukratis. Part I., 1884-85 (pl. XXXIII, no. 228)
Bernand 1970 / Le Delta égyptien d'après les textes grecs, i: les confins libyques (p. 662, no. 189)
Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (GE.945)
